meanings.type: Godan verb with 'su' ending, Transitive verb
meanings.meaning: 1. to take out; to get out お金がいくらか必要なら銀行から出してもよい。You can withdraw some money out of the bank, if you need any.

meanings.type: Godan verb with 'su' ending, Transitive verb
meanings.meaning: 2. to put out; to reveal; to show この件では名前を出したくない。I want to remain anonymous in this.

meanings.type: Godan verb with 'su' ending, Transitive verb
meanings.meaning: 3. to submit (e.g. thesis); to turn in 答案を出す前にもう一度読み返しなさい。Read over your paper before you hand it in.

meanings.type: Godan verb with 'su' ending, Transitive verb
meanings.meaning: 4. to publish; to make public See also あぶり出す あぶりだす１月２０日（月曜日）の午前中に最終の議事事項を出しますので、早急にお返事を下さい。We'll release the final agenda on the morning of Monday, January 20, so please reply quickly.

meanings.type: Godan verb with 'su' ending, Transitive verb
meanings.meaning: 5. to send (e.g. letter) See also 手紙を出すこの間投稿した記事がやっと雑誌に載ったんだよ。頑張って出し続けた甲斐があったよ。Sending manuscript after manuscript paid off. A magazine finally published my work.

meanings.type: Godan verb with 'su' ending, Transitive verb
meanings.meaning: 6. to produce (a sound); to start (fire) See also 声を出す政府は次のような声明を出した。The government issued the following statement.

meanings.type: Godan verb with 'su' ending, Transitive verb
meanings.meaning: 7. to serve (food) ここではおいしい食べ物が出されます。They serve excellent food here.
8. ... out (e.g. to jump out, to carry out) See also 飛び出す とびだす, after the -masu stem of a verbいつから痛みだしましたか。How long have you had this pain?
9. to begin ...; to start to ...; to burst into ... See also 歌いだす うたいだす, after the -masu stem of a verb
